    "attributes": {
        "action": "Staff training and mandatory support plan for school students with M.E.",
        "additional_details": "Myalgic encephalomyelitis (ME) is characterised by a range of neurological symptoms and signs, muscle pain with intense physical or mental exhaustion, relapses, and specific cognitive disabilities.\r\nM.E effects 250,000 people in the UK and 30,000,000 worldwide. \r\nM.E is one of the main causes of long term school absences in the UK.",
        "background": "I have had the \u201cinvisible illness\u201d Myalgic Encephalomyelitis (M.E/CFS) for nearly 3 years, it has affected my life massively from losing who I was, hobbies and my EDUCATION. I have missed a massive amount of education due to schools not accommodating my needs and lack of understanding and training.",
